{"word":"στείβω","slug":"στείβω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>στείβω</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to tread on, tread under foot</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> cogn. to tread or <i>walk on</i> a path, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; also, <el>χοροὺς στείβειν</el> <i>to tread</i> measures, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to tread</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to stamp down</i>, in <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b>; <el>αἱ στειβόμεναι ὁδοί</el> the <i>beaten</i> roads, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}